EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to forensic medical examinations; eliminating the authority of a
compensation officer appointed by the Director of the Department of
Health and Human Services to order the payment of compensation to
reimburse a county for the costs of certain forensic medical
examinations; requiring the State to pay [from the State General Fund]
, with certain limitations, the costs of a forensic medical examination
of a victim of a sexual assault or domestic violence battery by
strangulation; and providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law: (1) requires a county in whose jurisdiction a sexual assault is committed to
2 pay any costs incurred by a hospital for the forensic medical examination of the victim; and
3 (2) authorizes a compensation officer appointed by the Director of the Department of Health
4 and Human Services to order the payment of compensation to reimburse a county for the costs
5 of the forensic medical examination. (NRS 217.160, 217.300) Section 2 of this bill instead
6 requires the State to pay [from the State General Fund] , with certain limitations, the costs
7 for such a forensic medical examination. Section 1 of this bill eliminates the authority of a
8 compensation officer to order the payment of compensation to reimburse a county for the
9 costs of such a forensic medical examination.
10 Existing law requires a county in whose jurisdiction a domestic violence battery by
11 strangulation is committed to pay any costs incurred by a hospital for a strangulation forensic
12 medical examination of the victim. (NRS 217.405) Section 3 of this bill instead requires the
13 State to pay [from the State General Fund] , with certain limitations, the costs for such a
14 forensic medical examination.

